<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226812>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Cylindromacrostomum formosae n. sp .. A. The living animal, drawn from a micrograph. — B. Hard parts of the male copulatory system in the holotype. The asterix indicates the transparent lamella at the beginning of the straight terminal end. — C. Micrograph of the male copulatory organs in the holotype. — D. Terminal end of the penis stylet and of the accessory stylet in the holotype. — E. End part of the penis stylet in a paratype. — F-H. Hard parts in the female system in the holotype. — I-K. Hard parts in the female system in a paratype. (Scales = 20 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226812/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.226811>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Paromalostomum dubium. A. Living animal at low magnification. — B. Caudal end in the living animal. — C. Hard parts in the female system. — D. Hard part of the copulatory organs. — E. Micrograph showing terminal end of accessory stylet and of the penis stylet, indicated by an asterisk. (Scales = 20 µm)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/226811/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

